  "descriptionTxt": "*Who are we?*\n\nAt Bright, we've engineered cutting-edge software for accounting, payroll, tax, and practice management. We've assembled a team of top talent and stand ready to lead the industry with our superior software solutions and unparalleled customer support.\n\nWe're brilliant people creating brilliant software! Join us in our mission to create brilliant software that empowers businesses to reach new heights.\n\n*Opportunity:*\n\nAs a Front End Developer you will play a crucial role in creating engaging and responsive user interfaces for our web applications. You will work closely with our development team to implement and enhance the user experience of our applications. This role offers an excellent opportunity for professional growth and skill development within a collaborative and supportive work environment.\n\n*Key Responsibilities:*\n\n· *Front End Development:*\n* Collaborate with the development team to design, develop, and maintain front-end applications and components.\n* Implement interactive and responsive user interfaces for web applications.\n\n· *UI/UX Design Integration:*\n* Work closely with UI/UX designers to implement visually appealing and user-friendly interfaces.\n* Ensure seamless integration of design elements into the application.\n\n· *Cross-Functional Collaboration:*\n* Collaborate with back-end developers to integrate front-end components with server-side logic.\n* Engage in regular communication with other team members to ensure a cohesive and well-integrated product.\n\n· *Code Review and Optimization:*\n* Participate in code reviews to ensure code quality, adherence to best practices, and maintainability.\n* Identify and address performance bottlenecks and optimize front-end code for improved efficiency.\n\n*The Person:*\n* Experience building applications using front-end frameworks such as Vue or Nuxt.\n* Strong understanding of front-end technologies such as HTML, CSS, and JavaScript.\n* Experience with UI/UX design principles and the ability to translate design concepts into functional code.\n* Working knowledge of .NET development and C# programming language.\n* Strong problem-solving skills and attention to detail.\n* Good communication and teamwork skills.\n\n*Preferred Experience:*\n* Bachelor's degree in Computer Science, Software Engineering, or related field.\n* Familiarity with Nuxt framework and a willingness to learn and expand expertise in this area.\n* Knowledge of RESTful API integration.\n* Familiarity with version control systems (e.g., GitHub).\n* Exposure to agile development methodologies.\n\nJob Types: Full-time, Permanent\n\nSalary: £26,000.00-£30,000.00 per year\n\nBenefits:\n* Additional leave\n* Company pension\n* Cycle to work scheme\n* Discounted or free food\n* Health & wellbeing programme\n* On-site parking\n* Private medical insurance\n* Sick pay\n* Work from home\nSchedule:\n* Monday to Friday\nSupplemental pay types:\n* Bonus scheme\n\n\n\nEducation:\n* Bachelor's (preferred)\n\nExperience:\n* Vue.js: 1 year (required)\n\nWork authorisation:\n* United Kingdom (required)\n\nAbility to Commute:\n*  Warwick (required)\n\n\nWork Location: Hybrid remote in  Warwick",
