  "title": "Junior Software Developer",
  "employer": "MediaBase Direct Limited",
  "descriptionTxt": "*NO RECRUITMENT AGENCIES PLEASE:*\n\n*Who we are:*\n\nMediaBase Direct are one of the longest-serving members of the Data & Marketing Association (DMA), and for over 30 years, we have been providing compliant data & digital solutions to our customers.\n\n*Role*\n\nJoin our dynamic team and contribute to the enhancement of our flagship product, *e-Reception Book*. As a key member, you will play a vital role in the development of innovative features and the upkeep of our existing infrastructure. Embrace the creative freedom to shape and refine ideas, drawing inspiration from various design influences.\n\nThis role presents a unique opportunity for *continuous on-the-job learning*, allowing you to expand your skill set in a dynamic work environment. We are committed to supporting your success by providing you with all the necessary tools and resources to perform at your best.\n\n*Job Requirements:*\n* Proficiency with *Laravel* applications.\n* Proficiency of *MySQL* and how to write basic queries alongside Eloquent.\n* Working understanding of one or more front-end frameworks such as Vue or React.\n* A creative problem solver.\n* Ability to collaborate as a team player and adapt to changing conditions.\n* Enthusiastic attitude towards learning and growth.\n\n*Essential:*\n* PHP (Experience preferred)\n* MySQL (Experience preferred)\n* Javascript (Experience preferred)\n\n*Desirable (Not Mandatory):*\n* Vue\n* Typescript\n\nThis is an excellent opportunity for a junior developer to join our team, even if you haven't mastered every listed skill. We believe in fostering on-the-job learning and providing the necessary support to help you thrive in a dynamic work environment. If you're passionate about development and eager to grow, we encourage you to apply and embark on a rewarding journey with us.\n\n\n\n*Recruitment Process*\n* Introductory call with the Head of Product and the Technical Lead\n* Technical interview (in person/virtual) covering experience and technical understandings.\n\nMediaBase Direct are an equal opportunities employer; we do not prejudice against any race, age, gender or ethnic background. We pride ourselves on our diversity.\n\nJob Types: Full-time, Permanent\n\nSalary: *£28,000 - £32,000 per Annum (Based upon experience and skills)*\n\n*We are looking for multiple candidates.*\n\nBenefits:\n* Casual dress\n* Company pension\n* On-site parking\n* Work from home\n\nSchedule:\n* Monday to Friday\n\nSupplemental pay types:\n* Performance bonus\n\nExperience:\n* Laravel: 1 year (required)\n* PHP: 1 year (required)\n* MySQL: 1 year (required)\n\nWork Location: Hybrid remote in Portsmouth\n\nJob Type: Full-time\n\nSalary: £28,000.00-£32,000.00 per year\n\nBenefits:\n* Company pension\n* Free parking\n* On-site parking\n* Work from home\nSchedule:\n* Monday to Friday\nSupplemental pay types:\n* Bonus scheme\n\n\n\nEducation:\n* GCSE or equivalent (preferred)\n\nAbility to Commute:\n*  Fareham (required)\n\nAbility to Relocate:\n*  Fareham: Relocate before starting work (required)\n\n\nWork Location: Hybrid remote in  Fareham\n\n\nReference ID: MBD-JSW",
