  "title": "Full Stack Software Developer",
  "employer": "Advoco Solutions Ltd",
  "descriptionTxt": "*About Us*\n\nAdvoco Solutions are an IT consultancy company offering a suite of IT products and services to SMEs with the ultimate aim of increasing business productivity for our clients. We are long established, ambitious and are looking to expand, level up, and continue a sustained period of growth.\n\nWe are one of the Maximizer CRMs leading partners globally and are renowned internationally in the marketplace for our innovative bespoke CRM solutions based on our own highly customisable and low code, Synergy CRM offering.\n\n*About the Role*\n\nWe are seeking a skilled full stack developer to join our expanding team. You will be working as a part of a team that is responsible for designing, developing, and maintaining our Synergy CRM product and the solutions that we implement within and around it. The role requires ongoing learning and implementation of the latest technologies and methodologies.\n\nResponsibilities are to include:\n\n* Writing, testing, and maintaining product and customer specific code.\n* Direct communication with clients and team members to understand and gather requirements, and translate these into technical solutions.\n* Generating and maintaining technical documentation as required during projects.\n* Providing ongoing maintenance and support for applications, including troubleshooting and resolving issues post-deployment.\n\n*About you*\n\nTo be successful in this role, you should hold a degree in computer science and/or have relevant industry experience. In this role you will demonstrate:\n\n* Strong Proficiency with modern object-orientated programming methods and languages, particularly including Angular, Typescript, and C#.\n* Strong problem-solving and team working abilities\n* Familiarity with .Net Framework, Web API 2, Entity Framework and SQL Server.\n* Some experience of user interface design.\n* Understanding of unit testing, version control, and deployment processes.\n* Knowledge of SCRUM and agile software development processes.\n* Knowledge or experience of CRM would be advantageous.\n* Experience with cloud platforms such as Azure or AWS would also be beneficial.\n* Being within a 30 minute catchment of RG7 2PQ and a willingness to commute and be a part of the team will be a significant advantage.\n\nIf you are a talented Software Engineer looking for an exciting opportunity to work on innovative projects and contribute to the success of our company, we would love to hear from you. Apply today!\n\nNo agencies please.\n\nJob Type: Full-time\n\nSalary: £35,000.00-£45,000.00 per year\n\nBenefits:\n* Company pension\nSchedule:\n* Monday to Friday\n\n\n\nEducation:\n* GCSE or equivalent (preferred)\n\nAbility to Commute:\n* Reading, RG7 2PQ (required)\n\nAbility to Relocate:\n* Reading, RG7 2PQ: Relocate before starting work (required)\n\n\nWork Location: In person",
