  "title": "Software Developer",
  "employer": "D-Tech International",
  "descriptionTxt": "Software Developer\n\n*Job Description*\n\nWe are delighted to be recruiting for a Software Developer to join our in house development team. We are a company who has provide automated self-service hardware and software solutions since 2002. We primarily focus on the library industry but we are also looking to branch out in other areas of business, our solutions are typically based on .Net, C# and PHP web-development. We are looking for a candidate who is keen and enthusiastic to go above and beyond to get the job done! We welcome new ideas on improving our products and encourage our developers to bring these to the table.\n\nPart of this roll will also be helping support the Service Desk with any bug fixes that they encounter, software bugs will need to be resolved within SLA times depending on the level of severity and what is agreed with the customer in terms of their SLA.\n\n*Responsibilities:*\n\nYou will be working as a team to provide bug fixes, updates and further developments on all software applications answering to the Head of Software Development. Training on the software applications will be provided.\n\n*Skills:*\n\nExperience required with:\n\n- WPF\n\n- .NET\n\n- C#\n\n- ASP.NET\n\n- Azure\n\n- Experience with hardware integration\n* Passionate about software development\n* Capable of learning new skills quickly\n* Friendly and approachable\n* Trustworthy and reliable\n* Understanding of the responsibility that comes with having access to sensitive data\n* Able to communicate effectively both in written and verbal form\n\n*Desirable Skills:*\n* Xamarin\n* PHP\n* JavaScript\n* Experience of using Git Source Control\n* Fully conversant with Visual Studio IDE.\n* Writing application code interfacing to payment hardware and RFID hardware.\n\n*Package*\n* Salary from 25k depending on experience\n* An environment where your abilities can be nurtured and your opinions are welcomed\n* Training to fill the gaps in systems knowledge as required for the right candidate\n* A flexible and informal work environment\n* 20 days annual leave pro rata plus statutory bank holidays\n* 35-hour working week plus a 1-hour lunch break\n* Life Insurance scheme at work\n* Sick Pay\n\nPlease only apply if you are in commuting distance to our HQ, I'm afraid overseas applicants will be declined.\n\nJob Types: Full-time, Permanent\n\nSalary: £35,000.00 per year\n\nBenefits:\n* Company pension\n* Free parking\n* On-site parking\n* Sick pay\n* Work from home\nSchedule:\n* Monday to Friday\n\n\n\nApplication question(s):\n* Do you live within a 30 mile radius of Woodbridge, IP12 2TW?\n\nExperience:\n* C#/.NET: 2 years (required)\n\nWork authorisation:\n* United Kingdom (required)\n\nAbility to Commute:\n* Woodbridge, IP12 2TW (required)\n\n\nWork Location: In person",
