  "key": "f16f3a25fbd857eb",
  "title": "Software Test Engineer",
  "employer": "Purple Matrix Ltd",
  "descriptionTxt": "As our Test Engineer, you will be responsible for the testing of web applications. Working from initial software specifications you will develop and run test plans for customer acceptance testing, partner compliance, supporting software releases into production,\n\n*JOB SPECIFICATION*\n\n* Develop software test plans for the purpose of testing our products, resolving inconsistencies and issues.\n* Work closely with the APP development team.\n* Writing and executing test cases for new and existing functionality.\n* Interface to software developers and other teams to resolve issues and improve quality.\n* Working in the development of cutting-edge features and platforms as well as regression work with existing products.\n* Assist the production team with their requirements and with software releases as necessary.\n* Identify automated test opportunities and assist with implementation.\n* Raising bugs in a timely manner with sufficient detail to be fixed/reproduced.\n\n*SKILLS AND QUALIFICATIONS*\n\n* ISTQB Foundation Qualification or a degree in a related field.\n* Minimum 2 years of proven working experience as an Automation Tester with a focus on web applications.\n* Knowledge of automation testing tools ideally using Cypress with TypeScript / JavaScript or Selenium with Java.\n* Good Java / JavaScript / TypeScript knowledge.\n* Manual testing for the releases including System testing and Regression testing.\n* Well organised and able to work to tight deadlines – good time management.\n* Ability to work on own initiative and pickup things quickly.\n* Excellent communication skills and ability to communicate effectively with developers.\n* Great team player.\n* Problem solving and analytical skills to identify the root cause and resolve performance blockages.\n* Attention to detail.\n\n*REQUIRED EXPERIENCE*\n\n* Minimum 2 years software test experience.\n* Minimum 2 years of Automation Testing experience / knowledge is essential.\n* Ability to identify issues, accurately log and record defect records in a tracking system and progress through to closure.\n* Ideally have experience of using Microsoft Azure DevOps for bug tracking, reporting, and querying\n* Version control systems such as Git.\n* API testing using Postman/Newman\n* Working knowledge of web services\n* Working knowledge of test management software and SQL\n\n*PROFESSIONAL QUALIFICATIONS*\n\nWe are Microsoft Gold Partner and candidates with any current Microsoft qualifications certainly stand out from the crowd.\n\nJob Type: Full-time\n\nSalary: £30,000.00-£42,000.00 per year\n\nBenefits:\n* Additional leave\n* Casual dress\n* Company events\n* Cycle to work scheme\n* Flexitime\n* Referral programme\n* Work from home\nSchedule:\n* Day shift\n* Monday to Friday\n\n\n\nApplication question(s):\n* What is 'bug severity'\n* How do you know when it’s time to stop testing\n* You are mid-level professional at a software development department of a small company.\nWho should ideally set your goals at work?\n* You have a busy job and often run out of time to complete all your tasks. In particular, you must respond to some emails every day that typically only require a short and simple response, but you can’t seem to get these done during your normal day.\nHow should you handle responding to these emails?\n* 45 people in a certain company can work together to finish a project in 15 days. For a project of the same workload, the company decided to use 15 people. Assume all people have the same level of productivity.\nIn how many days the project can be completed?\n\n\nWork Location: Hybrid remote in London",
