  "key": "bb66483beaf90c50",
  "title": "Graduate Software Engineer",
  "employer": "Applause IT",
  "descriptionTxt": "Graduate Software Engineer\n\nFully Remote (UK)\n\nSalary - Up to £30,000\n\nApplause IT are hiring for a Graduate Software Engineer who has knowledge of C++ and Linux to work in a defence and security company, specifically working on their newest technology. You will have the chance to work for a Cyber Security company with 30 years' experience, developing code and software.\n\nThe right Graduate Software Engineer will be working to provide secure information exchange to companies spanning Europe and the US. With 4 in 10 businesses now reporting cyber security breaches, this industry is only going to grow. Developing code alongside doing some functional testing and validating development code. While understanding the customers need and then being able to produce designs and specifications to meet those requirements.\n\nDesired Skills:\n\nKnowledge of C++\nPreviously used Linux\nSecurity Clearable (UK)\n\nThis is a fantastic opportunity to join a well-respected company who are looking to grow in size, and stature. If you think you would be suitable for this role or would like to learn more about the role, then APPLY NOW! By calling me on 07935569749 or email me on george.clayton@applauseit.co.uk",
