  "key": "30c3f861d234588b",
  "title": "Senior Software Engineer",
  "employer": "Plumbworld (Online Home Retail Ltd.)",
  "descriptionTxt": "*Who we are*\n\nOnline Home Retail is the home of Plumbworld.co.uk and Plumbnation.co.uk, serving 1000s of customers both within the plumbing trade and general public.\n\nOur people make us who we are. We want you to enjoy and challenge yourself, build a career, and teach us what we don’t know. Our plans are ambitious, and we’re looking for people who want to join us for the ride – our growth will be your growth.\n\n*The role in short*\n\nWe are seeking a skilled Senior Software Engineer with expertise in C#, ASP.NET MVC, Web APIs and MSSQL to join our dynamic team. As a senior software engineer, you will take on a high level role in the development and maintenance of our software applications, providing expertise, guidance, and mentorship to junior team members and contributing to the technical direction of our projects. You will collaborate closely with cross-functional teams to drive the successful delivery of robust and high-quality software solutions. Ensuring that all software solutions meet high-quality standards and fulfil the needs of our customers.\n\n*Perks of the job*\n* Work your hours around you, as long as you get the job done you can work when is best for you!\n* 31 days holiday (including bank holidays) bookable in hours making it super flexible for you\n* The option to buy and sell annual leave, to suit your personal needs\n* £150 per year Wellbeing Allowance\n* Access to our online platform for e-learning resources, hundreds of retail discounts, cycle to work scheme and car scheme\n* Fancy a new bathroom? We offer attractive staff discount to you and your family!\n* Of course, we offer all the good stuff like life assurance, pension scheme, training and free onsite parking!\n* Free fruit onsite for employees, delivered weekly.\n\n*Onto the nitty gritty!*\n* Contribute to and lead the design and implementation of software solutions according to established specifications and best practices.\n* Participate in the complete software development lifecycle, including analysis, design, development, testing, and deployment.\n* Provide technical mentorship and guidance to junior team members, driving a culture of excellence and continuous learning within the team.\n* Collaborate with team members to troubleshoot and resolve complex technical issues as they arise.\n* Champion best practices in software development, including code reviews, testing, performance optimization, and documentation.\n* Stay updated on emerging technologies and trends to drive continuous improvement and innovation within the team.\n\n*We’d like to meet someone with*\n* Proven experience in software development with proficiency in C#, ASP.NET and Web APIs (5+ years)\n* Familiarity with database technologies – MSSQL and proficiency in writing effective queries\n* Adept problem-solving abilities and a commitment to staying at the forefront of technological advancements and industry best practices\n* Excellent communication and teamwork skills with the ability to collaborate effectively in diverse teams\n* Proven ability to provide mentorship to more junior members of the team and drive technical excellence\n* Skilled in reading third-party documentation and integrating with third-party systems\n\n*If this sounds like you, please apply!*\n\n_All applicants must be eligible to work in the UK and employment is subject to a satisfactory DBS check._\n\nJob Types: Full-time, Permanent\n\nSalary: £45,000.00-£70,000.00 per year\n\nBenefits:\n* Additional leave\n* Company pension\n* Cycle to work scheme\n* Employee discount\n* Flexitime\n* Free parking\n* Health & wellbeing programme\n* On-site parking\n* Work from home\nSchedule:\n* Day shift\n* Monday to Friday\n\n\n\nAbility to Commute:\n* Evesham, WR11 1GL (required)\n\nAbility to Relocate:\n* Evesham, WR11 1GL: Relocate before starting work (required)\n\n\nWork Location: Hybrid remote in Evesham, WR11 1GL",
