  "key": "e63854cf37d23998",
  "title": "Full-stack Developer",
  "employer": "Right Legal Group",
  "descriptionTxt": "*Who we’re looking for:*\n\nAn experienced, multi-disciplined Software Developer to work on our ambitious software development programme. Our development plans for 2024 include adding further functionality to the company CRM. We want you to be a self-starter who is highly organised, communicative and team oriented. This is a fantastic opportunity to shape and deliver the roadmap for system enhancements across the whole business.\n\n*Who are Right Legal Group?*\n\nWe are a well-established law firm, regulated by the SRA who specialise in Will, Probate & Estate Planning. We have built a network across the country which work together on a mission to change the way people think about making a Will and preserve not only our clients’ financial assets but their emotional assets too, for future generations. We are here to protect memories, not just money…\n\n*Would you like to help us to deliver on our mission? Here is what’s in it for you…*\n\nRight Legal Group provides:\n\n- *Career progression opportunities*. We pride ourselves on home-grown talent!\n\n- *Annual career planning platforms.* We want to hear all about you and your goals for the year & help you to facilitate your personal and professional ambitions.\n\n- A *company culture *that embodies empowerment and ownership. We don’t do hierarchy!\n\n- *Company ‘get togethers’*. There’s always something fun happening over here…\n\n- *Rewards & recognition programme.* You want to be recognised for your efforts? We love celebrating success.\n\n- *Westfield health benefits.* We want to promote your physical and mental health by giving 24/7 access to healthcare and other ‘healthy extras’ like discounted gym membership.\n\n*If this sounds like somewhere you can see yourself working, then read on to find out about the role.*\n\n*Key Competencies:*\n\n· Working with the rest of the business to deliver its core purpose and cultural values, driving the same thinking throughout the RLG network\n\n· Excellent verbal and written communication skills\n\n· ASP.NET Core 2.1+\n\n· C# / .NET\n\n· Vue.js (or other JavaScript framework)\n\n· Typescript\n\n· HTML5\n\n· CSS\n\n· Bootstrap\n\n· SQL Server\n\n· Azure WebApps\n\n· Azure SQL Databases\n\n· Azure Deployment\n\n· Docker\n\n*Desired:*\n\n· Blazor\n\n· UI/UX Development\n\n· Twilio\n\n· SendGrid\n\n· Sentry\n\n· Identity Server\n\n· Dapper\n\n· Entity Framework\n\n· Agile Processes\n\n· Knowledge and appreciation of GDPR\n\n*Salary:* £40k - £50k, dependent on experience\n\n*Job Location: *Wyvern Business Park, 16 Stanier Way, Derby DE21 6BF (Full-time, in person)\n\nJob Types: Full-time, Permanent\n\nSalary: £40,000.00-£50,000.00 per year\n\nBenefits:\n* Company events\n* Company pension\n* Free parking\n* On-site parking\nSchedule:\n* Monday to Friday\n\n\n\nExperience:\n* C#: 2 years (required)\n\nWork authorisation:\n* United Kingdom (required)\n\nAbility to Commute:\n*  Derby (required)\n\n\nWork Location: In person\n\n\nExpected start date: 01/05/2024",
